title: Archbishop 'shocked' at end of Syrian orphan scheme
text: show ad Britain is closing its doors to Syrian orphans to stop fuelling people trafficking routes, says ministers as Archbishop Welby says he's 'shocked and saddened' by the decision Home Secretary Amber Rudd says Dubs Amendment that opened Britain's doors to unaccompanied Syrian children was acting as a pull factor to more refugees Says cash-strapped councils lacked resources to cope with more child refugees Theresa May defends decision to close Dubs amendment and says it was only one of a number of routes by which vulnerable children could come to the UK Published: 15:06 GMT, 9 February 2017 | Updated: 17:49 GMT, 9 February 2017 49 shares
